  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Cardiovascular Disease
Type:        Metabolic
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Chest pain, shortness of breath
Treatment:   Statins, surgery, stents
Deaths/yr:   17.9M
Vaccine:     No (for most types)
Discovered:  Ancient

Disease:     Ebola
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Ebola virus
Transmission:Bodily fluids contact
Symptoms:    Fever, bleeding, organ failure
Treatment:   Monoclonal antibodies, supportive
Deaths/yr:   0.001M
Vaccine:     Yes (Ervebo for Zaire strain)
Discovered:  1976

Disease:     Cancer
Type:        Cellular
Pathogen:    Various causes
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Lumps, weight loss, fatigue
Treatment:   Chemo, surgery, immunotherapy
Deaths/yr:   10.0M
Vaccine:     Some (HPV, Hep B vaccines)
Discovered:  Ancient

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

